=========================================================================

This software listens for NACK (negative acknowledgement) datagrams from
Bitcoin SV (BSV) transaction shard listeners, retrieves the corresponding
cached BSV transaction frames, and retransmits each frame to the correct
IPv6 multicast group derived from the transaction ID.

=========================================================================
Conceptual Attribution

The IPv6 multicast transaction broadcast architecture from which this
software draws inspiration was articulated by Dr. Craig S. Wright:

  Multicast within Multicast: Anycast
  https://singulargrit.substack.com/p/multicast-within-multicast-anycast
  https://singulargrit.substack.com/

=========================================================================
Third-Party Standards

The v1 wire-frame format (FrameVerV1 = 0x01) accepted and retransmitted
by this software transports transactions conforming to BRC-12: Raw
Transaction Format, a published standard maintained by BSV Blockchain:

  BRC-12: Raw Transaction Format
  BSV Blockchain Standards Repository
  https://github.com/bitcoin-sv/BRCs/blob/master/transactions/0012.md

